OECD’s Gurria Backs Lagarde as IMF Chief, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 
2011-05-25T06:38:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/oecd-s-gurria-backs-lagarde-as-imf-chief-handelsblatt-says.html
Angel Gurria , secretary-general of
the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development, backs
French Finance Minister  Christine Lagarde  for the International
Monetary Fund’s top post,  Handelsblatt  reported.  In Lagarde, “the Europeans have definitely chosen their
best and smartest,” Gurria was cited by the newspaper as
saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Parkin in Berlin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  